<font color="#FF0000">WHY IS VIETNAM NOT TAUGHT?</font><br>
<tt>Tue Apr  1 15:06:01 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I am a freshman at Morehead State University and  a history major.  I am doing a research paper on Vietnam and the political motivations of the war.  I am interested in the war because I went through twelve years of public school and no one ever told me what happened in Vietnam.  I know everything there is to know about Mesopatamia in 800B.C. But I don't know what happened to my neighbors.  It angers me that the plight of the men who went to Vietnam  have been ignored in the schools.  I have the utmost respect for anyone who went to Vietnam.  Keep telling your stories so that the youth can learn from the tragedies that happenedto you.  I would like to hear from anyone who would like to tell me their story.  I am more than willing to listen!<br>

<p><code>-- mrdelo01@morehead-st.edu  (Misty) </code><p>


